'''姓名决定论'''（{{lang-en|Nominative determinism}}）是1994年《[[新科學人|新科學人]]》杂志率先提出的[[假说|假说]]，声称人类倾向根据姓名选择适合的职业方向。该杂志行文幽默的“反馈”专栏指出，许多研究人员的[[姓氏|姓氏]]与研究领域非常契合。例如[[丹尼尔·斯诺曼|丹尼尔·斯诺曼]]{{refn|group="注"|name="snowman"|“斯诺曼”原文“{{lang|en|Snowman}}”有“雪人”之意。}}曾出版极地探索著作，研究员斯普拉特{{refn|group="注"|name="Splatt"|“斯普拉特”原文“{{lang|en|Splatt}}”有“溅泼”之意。}}曾与他人合作发表泌尿学文章。结合类似事例，人们不禁猜测姓名与职业或存在心理关联。《新科学人》提出假说后持续收到读者反馈例证，据此不定期重新讨论主题。姓名决定论同[[标名|标名]]联系密切，但含义有区别。姓名决定论关注姓名与职业的因果关系，标名仅指人名同职业贴合，不考虑贴合原因。

[[西格蒙德·弗洛伊德|西格蒙德·弗洛伊德]]的姓氏有“快乐”之意，心理学家[[卡尔·荣格|卡尔·荣格]]据此提出人类倾向根据姓氏选择职业。少量现代实证研究表明，有些职业从业人员姓名与职业相符的比例很高，但这些研究的取样手段尚有争议。姓名决定论可能是[[内隐自大|内隐自大]]的产物，该假说认为人类会下意识地对自身相关事物感兴趣。

== 背景 ==
早在人类自行选择与姓名相符的工作前，许多人就因职业得名<ref name="Weekley">{{cite book | last = Weekley | first = Ernest | title = The Romance of Names | publisher = John Murray | location = London | year = 1914 | url = https://archive.org/details/romanceofnames00week | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>{{rp|2}}，人类起名思路随时代变化<ref name="Fowler-2012">{{cite book | last = Fowler | first = Alastair | title = Literary Names: Personal Names in English Literature | location = Oxford | publisher = Oxford University Press | year = 2012 | isbn = 978-0-19-165099-4}}</ref>{{rp|11}}。城市诞生前人们通常只有单名，如“伯恩哈德”（“{{lang|en|Beornheard}}”）就是常见的盎格鲁-撒克逊人名<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|68}}{{refn|group="注"|[[古羅馬人名|古羅馬人名]]几经变迁，开始是“罗穆卢斯”（“Romulus”）这类单名，此后14个世纪先演变成双名，再变成三名（如“[[西塞罗|马库斯·图利乌斯·西塞罗]]”，其中“马库斯”是首名，“图利乌斯”是氏族名，“西塞罗”是姓），再变回双名，最终回归单名<ref name="Salway">{{cite journal | last1 = Salway | first1 = Benet | title = What's in a Name? A Survey of Roman Onomastic Practice from c. 700 B.C. to A.D. 700 | journal = The Journal of Roman Studies | volume = 84 | pages = 124–145 | year = 1994 | doi = 10.2307/300873 | jstor = 300873}}</ref>{{rp|124–126}}。}}。取单名时通常考虑含义或当成[[綽號|昵称]]<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|68, 71}}。[[诺曼征服英格兰|诺曼征服英格兰]]后，英格兰人开始在单名后增加姓氏，此前只有少数人名包含不传给后代的绰号<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|68}}<ref>{{cite book | last = McKinley | first = Richard | title = A History of British Surnames | publisher = Taylor & Francis | year = 1990 | pages = 25–34}}</ref>，如“[[剛勇者愛德蒙|剛勇者愛德蒙]]”<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|68}}。姓氏先是根据人的身份所起，有些源于[[父名|父名]]，例如威廉之子约翰就叫“约翰·威廉姆森”{{refn|group="注"|“威廉姆森”原文“{{lang|en|Williamson}}”是“威廉”（“{{lang|en|William}}”）与“儿子”（“{{lang|en|son}}”）组合而成。}}）；有些是[[姓氏|职业描述]]，如“约翰·卡朋特”{{refn|group="注"|name="Carpenter"|“卡朋特”原文“{{lang|en|Carpenter}}”意为木匠。}}；有些代表性格或特点，如“约翰·隆”{{refn|group="注"|“隆”原文“{{lang|en|Long}}”意为“长”。}}；还有些是地点，例如名叫约翰的阿克顿人士就叫“约翰·阿克顿”<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|2}}。人类14世纪中期才逐渐开始把名字传给后人<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|viii}}，其中又以贸易、工艺相关姓氏率先进入传承，这主要是因为工艺往往在家族内部代代相传<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|143}}{{refn|group="注"|古罗马父辈把姓氏传给后代的也很常见<ref name="Salway" />{{rp|127}}。据盖乌斯·普林尼·塞孔杜斯（人称[[老普林尼|老普林尼]]）记载，源于职业的姓氏以农业最早，例如“西塞罗”意为“鹰嘴豆”，由此推断演说家马库斯·图利乌斯·西塞罗的先辈就靠种鹰嘴豆安身立命<ref>{{cite book | last = Wilson | first = Stephen | title = The Means Of Naming: A Social History | publisher = Routledge | location = London | year = 2003 | isbn = 978-1-135-36836-4 | page = 10}}</ref>；另有观点认为西塞罗的先辈是因鼻子形状像鹰嘴豆得名<ref>{{cite book | last = McKeown | first = J. C. | title = A Cabinet of Roman Curiosities: Strange Tales and Surprising Facts from the World's Greatest Empire | url = https://archive.org/details/cabinetofromancu0000mcke | location = Oxford | publisher = Oxford University Press | year = 2010 | access-date = 2022-03-24 | isbn = 978-0-19-975278-2 | page = 22}}</ref>。}}。商人不一定追随父辈脚步，故姓名与职业的匹配度随时间推移下降<ref name="Fowler-2012" />{{rp|11}}，例如14世纪的“香料商罗杰·卡朋特”{{refn|group="注"|name="Carpenter"}}<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|143}}。

除职业外，人们起名时往往重点考虑辞汇的广泛含义。17世纪英格兰人普遍认为给子孙取名要慎重，后辈应该根据姓名含义或包含的信息生活。<ref>{{cite book | last = Smith-Bannister | first = Scott | title = Names and Naming Patterns in England, 1538–1700 | publisher = Clarendon Press | location = Oxford | year = 1997 | isbn = 978-0-19-820663-7 | url = https://archive.org/details/namesnamingpatte0000smit | access-date = 2021-08-05 | page = 11}}</ref>1652年，英格兰神职人员[[威廉·詹金|威廉·詹金]]宣称，名字应当“像手指缠绕的线，提醒我们来到世上要为天神做什么”<ref>{{cite book | last = Jenkyn | first = William | title = Exposition of the epistle of Jude | year = 1652 | publisher = John Guilds and son | location = Bungay, England | url = https://archive.org/details/anexpositionupo01shergoog | access-date = 2021-08-05 | page = 7}}</ref>。1623年，[[清教徒|清教徒]]开始起名“费斯”{{refn|group="注"|“费斯”原文“{{lang|en|Faith}}”意为信仰。}}、“弗提图德”{{refn|group="注"|“弗提图德”原文“{{lang|en|Fortitude}}”意为坚韧。}}、“格雷斯”{{refn|group="注"|“格雷斯”原文“{{lang|en|Grace}}”意为恩典、慈悲、惠赐。}}，英格兰历史学家[[威廉·卡姆登|威廉·卡姆登]]宣称，人的行为可能受人名导向，所以应该选择含义“美好、亲切”的名字<ref>{{cite book | first = William | last = Camden | authorlink = 威廉·卡姆登 | editor-first = R. D. | editor-last = Dunn | title = Remains Concerning Britain | publisher = University of Toronto Press | place = Toronto | year = 1984 | isbn = 978-0-8020-2457-2 | access-date = 2021-08-05 | url = https://archive.org/details/remainsconcerni00camdgoog | page = 43}}</ref><ref name="Fowler-2012" />{{rp|14}}。随起[[大英帝国|大英帝国]]崛起，英语姓氏和起名思路传遍全球大部分地区<ref>{{cite book | author = American Council of Learned Societies | title = Surnames in the United States Census of 1790: An Analysis of National Origins of the Population | publisher = Genealogical Publishing Company | year = 1998 | location = Baltimore, Maryland | isbn = 978-0-8063-0004-7 | page = 180}}</ref>。

20世纪初，英语三大姓氏有两个源自职业，分别是“史密斯”{{refn|group="注"|name="Smith"|“史密斯”原文“{{lang|en|Smith}}”意为铁匠。}}和“泰勒”{{refn|group="注"|name="tailor"|“泰勒”原文“{{lang|en|Taylor}}”源自“{{lang|en|tailor}}”（发音相同），意为“裁缝”。}}，不过确是铁匠或裁缝的没几个<ref name="Weekley" />{{rp|43–44}}{{refn|group="注"|许多父系姓氏消失在历史长河，极少数姓氏人数众多。主要影响因素包括男童人数、移民、女人出嫁后改随夫姓等。[[朝鲜族姓氏列表|朝鲜族]]姓“[[金姓_(朝鮮)|金]]”、“[[李姓|李]]”、“[[朴姓|朴]]”的占四成三。以[[法蘭西斯·高爾頓|法蘭西斯·高爾頓]]和[[亨利·威廉·沃森|亨利·威廉·沃森]]命名的[[高尔顿-沃森过程|高尔顿-沃森过程]]以数学手段模拟姓氏延续几率，其中假设每对夫妇无子、一子和二子的几率均为三分之一，经计算认定三分之二的姓氏会在四代人内绝种。<ref>{{cite book | last = Ratzan | first = Lee | title = Understanding Information Systems: What They Do and why We Need Them | url = https://archive.org/details/understandinginf00ratz | publisher = American Library Association | location = Chicago | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-0-8389-0868-6 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/understandinginf00ratz/page/n136 120]–122}}</ref>}}。姓名与职业的确出现对应关系时便引起关注，1888年《肯特人记事本》杂志列出名单，其中好几位运货马车夫叫“卡特”{{refn|group="注"|“卡特”原文“{{lang|en|Carter}}”意为运货马车夫。}}，经营男式紧身裤的叫“霍塞戈德”{{refn|group="注"|“霍塞戈德”原文“{{lang|en|Hosegood}}”是“男式紧身裤”（“{{lang|en|hose}}”）与“商品”（“{{lang|en|goods}}”）组合而成。}}，拍卖商叫“塞尔斯”{{refn|group="注"|“塞尔斯”原文“{{lang|en|Sales}}”意为“销售”。}}，还有叫“卡夫”的布料经销商{{refn|group="注"|“卡夫”的原文“{{lang|en|Cuff}}”有袖口、裤子翻边之意。}}<ref name="F2000">{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | accessdate = 2022-03-24 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg16622395-600-feedback/ | date = 2000-05-19 | issue = 2239 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308132546/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg16622395-600-feedback/ | archivedate = 2021-03-08}}</ref>。此后，各种指代姓名与职业密切关系的名词应运而生。“标名”据信是20世纪初美国报纸专栏作家[[富兰克林·亚当斯|富兰克林·亚当斯]]所创，<ref>{{cite book | last = Safire | first = William | title = No Uncertain Terms: More Writing from the Popular "On Language" Column in The New York Times Magazine | access-date = 2022-03-24 | page = 18 | url = https://archive.org/details/nouncertainterms0000safi | location = New York | publisher = Simon and Schuster | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-0-7432-5812-8}}</ref>语言学家弗兰克·纽塞尔1992年新创“{{lang|en|aptonym}}”，与亚当斯的“标名”原文“{{lang|en|aptronym}}”相比只缺字母“{{lang|en|r}}”<ref>{{cite book | last = Nuessel | first = Frank | title = The Study of Names | url = https://archive.org/details/studyofnamesguid0000nues | publisher = Greenwood Press | location = Santa Barbara, California | year = 1992 | isbn = 978-0-313-28356-7 | access-date = 2022-03-24}}</ref>。其他同义词如“{{lang|en|euonym}}”<ref>{{cite book | last = Room | first = Adrian | title = An Alphabetical Guide to the Language of Name Studies | year = 1996 | publisher = Scarecrow Press | location = Lanham, Maryland | isbn = 978-0-8108-3169-8 | page = 40}}</ref>、“{{lang|en|Perfect Fit Last Name}}”（字面意“完美契合姓氏”，简称“{{lang|en|PFLN}}”)<ref name="Levey-1985">{{cite news | last = Levey | first = Bob | title = Bob Levey's Washington | newspaper = [[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]] | date = 1985-11-20 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2020-07-30 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200730230855/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1985/11/20/bob-leveys-washington/48bf48da-ce02-4f96-825a-18e7ea528059/ | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1985/11/20/bob-leveys-washington/48bf48da-ce02-4f96-825a-18e7ea528059/ }}</ref>、“{{lang|en|namephreak}}”<ref name="Conrad">{{cite book | last = Conrad | first = Barnaby | title = The World of Herb Caen: San Francisco 1938–1997 | year = 1999 | publisher = Chronicle Books | url = https://archive.org/details/worldofherbcaens0000unse | access-date = 2021-08-05 | location = San Francisco | isbn = 978-0-8118-2575-7 | pages = 16–17}}</ref>。[[文学批评|文艺研究]]领域把姓名与人物特征非常契合的情况称为“个性化诨名”<ref>{{cite book | author = Merriam-Webster | title = Merriam-Webster's Encyclopedia of Literature | publisher = Merriam-Webster | location = Springfield, Massachusetts | year = 1995 | isbn = 978-0-87779-042-6 | page = 229 | url = https://archive.org/details/merriamwebsters00merr | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>，许多名家经常采用这种文体手段，如[[查尔斯·狄更斯|查尔斯·狄更斯]]就在《[[艰难时世|艰难时世]]》为满心算计的专横校长起名“葛擂硬”{{refn|group="注"|“葛擂硬”原文“{{lang|en|Gradgrind}}”是“评分”（“{{lang|en|grad}}”）与“折磨”（{{lang|en|grind}}）结合而成。}}<ref>{{cite book | last = Lederer | first = Richard | title = Crazy English | publisher = Simon and Schuster | location = New York | year = 2010 | isbn = 978-1-4391-3894-6 | page = 67}}</ref>；[[威廉·莎士比亚|威廉·莎士比亚]]在《[[冬天的故事|冬天的故事]]》为流落民间的公主起名“珀迪塔”，该名源自拉丁语，意为“流失者”<ref>{{cite book | last = Cavill | first = Paul | chapter = Language-based approaches to names in literature | editor-last = Hough | editor-first = Carole | title = The Oxford Handbook of Names and Naming | series =Oxford Handbooks in Linguistics Series | publisher = Oxford University Press | location = Oxford | year = 2016 | isbn = 978-0-19-965643-1 | page = 365}}</ref>。有些人名意在逗趣，如[[约瑟夫·海勒|约瑟夫·海勒]]著作《[[第22条军规|第22条军规]]》人物[[梅杰·梅杰·梅杰少校|梅杰·梅杰·梅杰少校]]，父亲给他取名“梅杰·梅杰·梅杰”，入伍后军方配备的[[IBM|IBM]][[电子计算机|计算机]]“幽默感像他父亲一般敏锐”，马上就把他晋升[[少校|少校]]{{refn|group="注"|“梅杰”原文与“少校”一样是“{{lang|en|Major}}”，人物原名“{{lang|en|Major Major Major}}”，加上军衔就变成“{{lang|en|Major Major Major Major}}”。}}<ref>{{cite book | last = Heller | first = Joseph | author-link = 约瑟夫·海勒 | title = Catch-22 | url = https://archive.org/details/catch22novelhell00hell | year = 1961 | orig-year = republished 1999 | publisher = Simon & Schuster | location = New York | isbn = 9780684865133 | access-date = 2021-08-05 | page = 85}}</ref>。标名不考虑因果关系，如为什么-{}-姓名与职业相符，这与“姓名决定论”不同<ref name="Michalos">{{cite journal | last = Michalos | first = Christina | title = In the Name of the Law | journal = Counsel | volume = 25 | issue = 4 | pages = 16–18 | year = 2009 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2021-03-01 | url = https://www.5rb.com/article/in-the-name-of-the-law-nominative-determinism/ | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210301170226/https://www.5rb.com/article/in-the-name-of-the-law-nominative-determinism/}}</ref>。

标名的幽默潜力引起许多报纸关注。《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》专栏作家[[赫布·凯恩|赫布·凯恩]]不定期公布读者提供的例证，代课教师“菲林”{{refn|group="注"|“菲林”原文“{{lang|en|Fillin}}”有替工之意。}}、钢琴教师“帕提恩斯·斯盖尔斯”{{refn|group="注"|“帕提恩斯·斯盖尔斯”原文“{{lang|en|Patience Scales}}”第一个词意为“耐心”、第二个词意为“音阶”。}}、鼓吹摇滚乐邪恶论的[[聖座|聖座]]代言人“卡迪纳尔·拉普松”{{refn|group="注"|“卡迪纳尔·拉普松”原文“Cardinal Rapsong”第一个词意为“红衣主教”，第二个词指“说唱歌曲”。}}<ref name="Conrad" />。鲍勃·列维有时也在《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》专栏刊登读者发来的例子，如食品业顾问“费斯·波普康”{{refn|group="注"|“费斯·波普康”原文“{{lang|en|Faith Popcorn}}”第一个单词意为“信仰”，第二个单词意为“爆米花”。}}、名叫“萨金特”的部队中尉{{refn|group="注"|“萨金特”原文“{{lang|en|Sergeant}}”意为军士、中士。}}、税务会计师“谢尔比·戈德格拉布”{{refn|group="注"|“谢尔比·戈德格拉布”的姓氏“戈德格拉布”原文“{{lang|en|Goldgrab}}”是“黄金”（“{{lang|en|gold}}”）与“抢夺”（“{{lang|en|grab}}”）组合而成。}}<ref name="Levey-1985" /><ref>{{cite news | last = Levey | first = Bob | title = Bob Levey's Washington | newspaper = The Washington Post | archivedate = 2020-07-30 | date = 2000-08-29 | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/2000/08/29/a-new-batch-of-perfect-fit-last-names/92951cce-16fb-4fae-b21d-7dca0c78d9b2/ | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200730230853/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/2000/08/29/a-new-batch-of-perfect-fit-last-names/92951cce-16fb-4fae-b21d-7dca0c78d9b2/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。荷兰《[[誓言报|誓言报]]》提供不定期专栏“名即标志”{{refn|group="注"|原文{{lang|la|Nomen est omen}}是拉丁语，据信是罗马剧作家[[普劳图斯|普劳图斯]]首创<ref name="Michalos" />{{rp|3}}。}}，公布荷兰语姓名与职业相符的例证<ref>{{cite news | last = Hoekstra | first = Hans | title = Nomen est omen | newspaper = Het Parool | date = 2011-04-16 | page = 45 | archive-date = 2021-02-25 | url = https://www.meertens.knaw.nl/cms/files/Familienamen,%20Parool%20160411.pdf | access-date = 2021-08-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210225155716/https://www.meertens.knaw.nl/cms/files/Familienamen,%20Parool%20160411.pdf | dead-url = no | format = PDF}}</ref>。姓名收藏爱好者不甘人后，出版标名著作<ref>{{cite book | last = Dickson | first = Paul | title = What's in a name?: Reflections of an Irrepressible Name Collector | publisher = Merriam-Webster | url = https://archive.org/details/whatsinnamerefle00dick | location = Springfield, Massachusetts | year = 1996 | isbn = 978-0-87779-613-8 | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref><ref name="Hoekstra">{{cite book | last = Hoekstra | first = Hans | title = Naam & Faam | publisher = Nijgh & Van Ditmar | location = Amsterdam | year = 2001 | isbn = 978-90-388-3107-7 | page = 1}}</ref>。[[专有名词学|专有名词]]学者伦内克呼吁进一步验证报纸专栏与图书刊登的标名事例<ref>{{cite journal | last = Rennick | first = R.M. | title = The Alleged "Hogg Sisters", or Simple Ground Rules for Collectors of "Odd" Names | journal = Names | volume = 30 | issue = 3 | year = 1982 | page = 193 | doi = 10.1179/nam.1982.30.3.193}}</ref>，科学、医学、法律著作往往参考文献易于验证，列出的标名更可信<ref name="Keaney">{{cite journal | last1 = Keaney | first1 = John J. | last2 = Groarke | first2 = John D. | last3 = Galvin | first3 = Zita | last4 = McGorrian | first4 = Catherine | last5 = McCann | first5 = Hugh A. | last6 = Sugrue | first6 = Declan | last7 = Keelan | first7 = Edward | last8 = Galvin | first8 = Joseph | last9 = Blake | first9 = Gavin | last10 = Mahon | first10 = Niall G. | last11 = O'Neill | first11 = James | title = The Brady Bunch? New evidence for nominative determinism in patients' health: retrospective, population based cohort study | journal = [[英国医学期刊|British Medical Journal]] | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210714164803/https://www.bmj.com/content/347/bmj.f6627 | archivedate = 2021-07-14 | url = https://www.bmj.com/content/347/bmj.f6627 | year = 2013 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.f6627 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last = Bennett | first = H. J. | title = A piece of my mind. Calling Dr Doctor | journal = [[美国医学会杂志|JAMA]] | volume = 268 | issue = 21 | page = 3060 | year = 1992 | pmid = 1306061 | doi = 10.1001/jama.268.21.3060}}</ref>。

== 定义 ==
姓名决定论假说声称人类倾向根据姓名选择适合的职业方向<ref name="Alter">{{cite book | last = Alter | first = Adam | title = Drunk Tank Pink: And Other Unexpected Forces That Shape How We Think, Feel, and Behave | url = https://archive.org/details/drunktankpinksub0000alte | publisher = Penguin Press | location = London | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-1-78074-264-9 | pages = 7, 230 | access-date = 2022-03-24}}</ref>。人们可能是在潜意识影响下选择与姓名相符的工作。姓名决定论与标名的主要区别在于前者关注因果关系。<ref name="Michalos" />

1994年英国《[[新科學人|新科學人]]》杂志“回馈”专栏率先提出姓名决定论，主编约翰·霍兰德在11月5日的杂志写道：
{{quote|我们最近偶然看到新书《极地方位——两极地区与地球未来》，作者是丹尼尔·斯诺曼{{refn|group="注"|name="snowman"}}<ref>{{cite book | last = Snowman | first = Daniel | title = Pole Positions: Polar Regions and the Future of the Planet | url = https://archive.org/details/polepositionspol0000snow | publisher = Hodder & Stoughton | location = London | year = 1993 | isbn = 978-0-340-54068-8 | access-date = 2022-03-24}}</ref>。几周前我们又收到理查德·特伦奇等人的著作《伦敦城下的伦敦——地下世界指南》{{refn|group="注"|作者姓氏“特伦奇”原文“{{lang|en|Trench}}”有“沟渠”之意。}}<ref>{{cite book | last = Trench | first = Richard | title = London Under London: A Subterranean Guide | publisher = John Murray | location = London | year = 1993 | isbn = 978-0-7195-5288-5 | edition = 2}}</ref>。[[曼彻斯特大学|曼彻斯特大学]]的詹·亨特在十月《[[心理学家_(杂志)|心理学家]]》 发文称：“作家倾向选择与姓氏相符的研究领域”，结合上述事例显得很有意思<ref>{{cite journal | last = Hunt | first = Jen | title = The Psychology of Reference Hunting | journal = The Psychologist | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200620093736/https://thepsychologist.bps.org.uk/system/files/psy7no10.pdf | volume = 7 | issue = 10 | page = 480 | year = 1994 | url = https://thepsychologist.bps.org.uk/system/files/psy7no10.pdf | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2020-06-20 | format = PDF | accessdate = 2020-06-20}}</ref>。亨特援引《英国泌尿科期刊》文章为例，作者分别姓“斯普拉特”和“威登”{{refn|group="注"|name="Splatt"}}<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/j.1464-410X.1977.tb04095.x | last1 = Splatt | first1 = A. J. | last2 = Weedon | first2 = D. | title = The Urethral Syndrome: Experience with the Richardson Urethroplasty | journal = British Journal of Urology | volume = 49 | issue = 2 | pages = 173–176 | year = 1977 | pmid = 870138}}</ref>。<br/>我们感觉现在应当仔细论证，在此邀请各位提供科技领域实例（请附上佐证），以及您对这种情况发生原因的看法<ref name="F19941105">{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419506-000-feedback/ | date = 1994-11-05 | issue = 1950 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210408135819/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419506-000-feedback/ | archive-date = 2021-04-08 | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>。}}
“反馈”专栏主编霍兰德与迈克·霍尔德内斯随后采纳读者卡沃纽斯提出的“姓名决定论”为假说命名，在12月17日《新科学人》首度刊发<ref name="Alter" />。此后数十年间杂志多次想要中止话题<ref name="F2015">{{cite journal | title = Feedback: Scatological scorecards | journal = New Scientist | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2021-03-09 | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22630240-900-feedback-scatological-scorecards/ | date = 2015-06-03 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | issue = 3024 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210309075313/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22630240-900-feedback-scatological-scorecards/}}</ref>，但读者持续发来引人好奇的范例，如回答记者事涉[[关塔那摩湾拘押中心|关塔那摩湾拘押中心]]提问的美国海军发言人麦克·卡夫卡中校{{refn|group="注"|奥匈帝国作家[[弗朗茨·卡夫卡|弗朗茨·卡夫卡]]以描述孤立无援、仿佛噩梦的世界闻名。}}<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | archive-date = 2021-05-06 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg18324556-900-feedback/ | date = 2004-07-09 | issue = 2455 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210506181131/http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg18324556-900-feedback/ | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>，《帝国动物》的作者莱昂内尔·泰格尔{{refn|group="注"|“莱昂内尔·泰格尔”原文“{{lang|en|Lionel Tiger}}”第一个词源自“狮子”（“{{lang|en|lion}}”），第二个词意为“老虎”（“{{lang|en|tiger}}”）。}}与罗宾·福克斯{{refn|group="注"|“罗宾·福克斯”原文“{{lang|en|Robin Fox}}”第一个词意为“知更鸟”，第二个词意为“狐狸”<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | archivedate = 2021-03-08 | deadurl = no | issue = 2525 | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg18825251-500-feedback/ | date = 2005-11-09 | accessdate = 2021-03-08 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308204142/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg18825251-500-feedback/}}</ref>。}}，英国警察局长协会刀具罪案科发言人阿尔弗雷德·希区柯克{{refn|group="注"|与[[亞弗列·希治閣|知名恐怖片导演]]同名。}}<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | access-date = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19426032-500-feedback/ | date = 2007-05-09 | issue = 2603 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308142541/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19426032-500-feedback/ | archivedate = 2021-03-08}}</ref>。

自《新科学人》提出假说伊始，“姓名决定论”就专指姓名与职业相符的情况<ref name="F19941105" /><ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419566-600-feedback/ | date = 1994-12-17 | issue = 1956 | archivedate = 2020-11-11 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111220353/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419566-600-feedback/}}</ref><ref name="F2000" /><ref name="F2015" />。杂志编辑向其他报纸投稿时大多坚持上述范围，仅罗杰·海菲尔德在《[[标准晚报|标准晚报]]》的专栏还包含“人生关键特征”<ref>{{cite news | last = Highfield | first = Roger | title = The name game - the weird science of nominative determinism | url = https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/the-name-game-the-weird-science-of-nominative-determinism-6384728.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210506020927/http://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/the-name-game-the-weird-science-of-nominative-determinism-6384728.html | newspaper = The Evening Standard | date = 2011-03-24 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2021-05-06}}</ref><ref name="Colls">{{cite news | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_9664000/9664697.stm | title = When the name fits the job | first = Tom | last = Colls | date = 2011-12-20 | newspaper = BBC Radio 4 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210327002843/http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_9664000/9664697.stm | archivedate = 2021-03-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2022-03-24 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/8967602/A-persons-surname-can-influence-their-career-experts-claim.html | title = A person's surname can influence their career, experts claim | newspaper = The Telegraph | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112033038/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/8967602/A-persons-surname-can-influence-their-career-experts-claim.html | date = 2011-12-20}}</ref>{{refn|group="注"|还有研究人员扩大研究范围，基尼等研究员撰文《布拉迪成堆？病人健康领域提供姓名决定论新证据》，研究课题是名叫布拉迪的人有多少因患[[心跳过缓|心跳过缓]]装有起搏器，其中“心跳过缓”原文“{{lang|en|bradycardia}}”相当于“布拉迪”（{{lang|en|Brady}}）结合“心脏病患者”（“{{lang|en|cardia}}”）<ref name="Keaney" />。}}。

《新科学人》提出假说前，已有其他辞汇指代类似心理影响。[[罗伯塔·弗兰克|罗伯塔·弗兰克]]早在1970年就提出“专有名词决定论”<ref>{{cite journal | first = Roberta | last = Frank | title = Onomastic Play in Kormakr's Verse: the name Steingerðr | journal = Mediaeval Scandinavia | volume = 3 | year = 1970 | page = 25}}</ref>。德国心理学家[[威廉·斯特克尔|威廉·斯特克尔]]1911年提出“名字义务论”<ref name="Stekel">{{Cite journal | last = Stekel | first = Wilhelm | title = Die Verpflichtung des Namens | journal = Zeitschrift für Psychotherapie und medizinische Psychologie | volume = 3 | page = 110 | year = 1911}}</ref>。[[湯姆·斯托帕德|湯姆·斯托帕德]]1972年剧作《[[江珀_(剧作)|江珀]]》提出“姓氏综合症”<ref>{{cite book | last = Stoppard | first = Tom | title = Jumpers | year = 1972 | publisher = Faber & Faber | location = London | isbn = 978-0-571-14569-0 | page = 52 | url = https://archive.org/details/jumpers0000stop_d5b8 | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>。[[古罗马|古罗马]]时期人们就用拉丁短语“{{lang|la|nomen est omen}}”代指人名的预测功能，短语意为“名即标志”<ref name="Michalos" />，在英语<ref name="Michalos" />、法语<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Fibbi | first1 = Rosita | first2 = Bülent | last2 = Kaya | first3 = Etienne | last3 = Piguet | title = Nomen est omen: quand s' appeler Pierre, Afrim ou Mehmet fait la différence | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210228082258/http://www.snf.ch/SiteCollectionDocuments/nfp/nfp43_piguet_synthesis3.pdf | url = http://www.snf.ch/SiteCollectionDocuments/nfp/nfp43_piguet_synthesis3.pdf | publisher = Fonds National Suisse, Direction du programme PNR43 | location = Bern | year = 2003 | isbn = 978-3-908117-69-8 | format = [[便携式文档格式|PDF]] | archivedate = 2021-02-28 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | page = 0}}</ref>、德语<ref>{{cite book | last = Schaffer-Suchomel | first = Joachim | title = Nomen est Omen: Die verborgene Botschaft der Vornamen - Von Adam bis Zarah | location = Munich | publisher = Goldmann Arkana | year = 2009 | isbn = 978-3-641-01672-2 | page = 1}}</ref>、意大利语<ref>{{cite book | last = Gerber | first = Sophia | title = Nomen est omen - Morfologia dei nomi propri di persona italiani | publisher = GRIN Verlag | location = Munich | year = 2006 | isbn = 978-3-638-56044-3 | page = 0}}</ref>、荷兰语<ref name="Hoekstra" />、斯洛文尼亚语沿用至今<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Duša | first1 = Zdravko | last2 = Kenda | first2 = Marjetka | title = Nomen est omen: Čiginj in njegova imena | publisher = Myra Locatelli | location = Volče, Slovenia | year = 2011 | isbn = 978-961-92522-5-3 | page = 0}}</ref>。

《新科学人》为姓名与职业冲突的情况造词“反姓名决定论”，如安德鲁·沃特豪斯之名与职业葡萄酒教授毫无关系<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback: A whole world of Tweet | journal = New Scientist | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22329791-000-feedback-a-whole-world-of-tweettm/ | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112015008/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22329791-000-feedback-a-whole-world-of-tweettm/ | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | date = 2014-07-23 | issue = 2979}}</ref>，准备当医生的托马斯·爱德华·基尔随后改姓“吉尔格森”{{refn|group="注"|姓氏“基尔”原文“{{lang|en|Kill}}”意为“杀害”。}}<ref>{{cite journal | last = Slovenko | first = R. | title = The Destiny Of A Name | journal = Journal of Psychiatry and Law | volume = 11 | issue = 2 | page = 227 | year = 1983 | s2cid = 166215791}}</ref>，马尼拉大主教[[辛海棉|辛海棉]]{{refn|group="注"|辛海棉原名“{{lang|en|Cardinal Sin}}”，第一个词意为“红衣主教”，第二个词意为“罪孽”，两词放在一起意为“头等大罪”。}}<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg15220568-300-feedback/ | date = 1996-11-16 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308150748/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg15220568-300-feedback/ | archivedate = 2021-03-08 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | issue = 2056}}</ref>。此外，《新科学人》多年来从不同方向探讨姓名决定论，如“拟声词姓名决定论”就以[[欧洲空间局|欧洲空间局]]首席任务科学家[[伯纳德·福英|伯纳德·福英]]为例<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19225722-300-feedback/ | date = 2006-10-04 | issue = 2572 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308105713/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19225722-300-feedback/ | archivedate = 2021-03-08}}</ref>；又如“姓名不确定论”，实例包括成千上万的科学论文，作者姓氏既有“王”，又有“赖特”{{refn|group="注"|“王”的英语“Wong”发音类似“{{lang|en|wrong}}”，意为“错误”；“赖特”的英语“{{lang|en|Wright}}”发音类似“{{lang|en|right}}”，意为“正确”。}}<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback: All shall have pills | journal = New Scientist | archivedate = 2021-03-08 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22129571-800-feedback-all-shall-have-pills/ | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308143424/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22129571-800-feedback-all-shall-have-pills/ | date = 2014-02-19 | issue = 2957 | accessdate = 2021-08-05}}</ref>；还有“职业优先论”，意指人的品味受职业影响，如警察喜欢[[约翰·康斯特勃|约翰·康斯特勃]]的画作，画家姓氏原文“{{lang|en|Constable}}”意为“警员”<ref>{{cite journal | title = Feedback | journal = New Scientist | access-date = 2021-08-05 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg16422087-200-feedback/ | date = 1999-10-15 | issue = 2208 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308170237/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg16422087-200-feedback/ | archivedate = 2021-03-08}}</ref>。部分文献还曾以同义词“{{lang|en|inaptronym}}”指代“反姓名决定论”<ref>{{cite news | last = Nunn | first = Gary | title = Reckless by name, reckless by nature? | newspaper = [[卫报|The Guardian]] | url = https://www.theguardian.com/media/mind-your-language/2014/oct/31/mind-your-language-nominative-determinism | date = 2014-10-31 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210307103120/https://www.theguardian.com/media/mind-your-language/2014/oct/31/mind-your-language-nominative-determinism | archivedate = 2021-03-07 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 研究 ==
=== 理论框架 ===
德国心理学家20世纪初就开始探讨姓名对决策的影响，是率先涉足该领域的科学家<ref>{{cite journal | last = Flugel | first = Ingeborg | title = On the significance of names | journal = British Journal of Medical Psychology | volume = 10 | issue = 2 | year = 1930 | page = 208 | doi = 10.1111/j.2044-8341.1930.tb01017.x}}</ref>。斯特克尔以强迫行为和职业选择为背景提出“姓名义务论”<ref name="Stekel" />；[[卡尔·亚伯拉罕|卡尔·亚伯拉罕]]认为，如果先祖的姓名与职业契合，继承事业的后辈就可能受姓名导向作用显著影响。他进一步推断，如果姓名与职业契合，家族可能会在一定程度上尽力实现名字代表的抱负。<ref>{{cite book | last = Abraham | first = Karl | title = Clinical Papers and Essays on Psychoanalysis | chapter = On determining the power of names (1911) | page = 31 | publisher = Karnac Books | location = London | year = 1979 | isbn = 978-1-78181-144-3}}</ref>1952年[[卡尔·荣格|卡尔·荣格]]在[[共時性|共時性]]理论著作援引斯特克尔的说法，著作理论代表没有因果关系却看似存在某种关联的事物<ref name="Jung">{{cite book | last = Jung | first = Carl | title = Synchronicity – An Acausal Connecting Principle | url = https://archive.org/details/synchronicityaca0000jung | year = 1972 | isbn = 978-0-7100-7397-6 | publisher = Routledge and Kegan Paul | location = London | access-date = 2022-03-24 | pages = 15, 27}}</ref>：

{{Quote|斯特克尔的“姓名强迫论”令我们颇感进退两难，他的话意指人名有时与个人特征或职业联系异常紧密，已经不能用巧合解释。例如……食品官员费斯特先生（原名意为肥壮）、律师霍斯崔德先生（原名意指为人精明、善于讨价还价）、产科医师卡尔弗先生（原名意为接生小牛犊的人）……这些究竟纯属偶然，还是正如斯特克尔所说的那样源自姓名暗示，亦或都是“有意义的巧合”？<ref name="Jung" />}}

荣格以包括他在内的知名心理学家为例：“[[西格蒙德·弗洛伊德|弗洛伊德]]（意为快乐）先生擅长[[超越快樂原則|快乐原则]]，[[格哈德·阿德勒|阿德勒]]（意为老鹰）精通权力意志，荣格（意为年纪小）专攻重生……<ref name="Jung" />”

心理学家劳伦斯·卡斯勒1975年呼吁实证研究职业与姓名相符的频率，确定姓名到底会不会影响职业选择，亦或一切不过“[[福尔图娜|幸运女神]]的引诱”。他对效应提出三种解释：一、人的自我形象与期望受姓名内在影响；二、姓名在他人口中形成期望，刺激主人达成；三、遗传因素：职业与关系密切的姓氏经家族世代相传。<ref>{{cite journal | last = Casler | first = Lawrence | title = Put the Blame on Name | journal = Psychological Reports | volume = 36 | issue = 2 | page = 472 | year = 1975 | url = https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/pdf/10.2466/pr0.1975.36.2.467 | doi = 10.2466/pr0.1975.36.2.467 | access-date = 2021-08-05 | s2cid = 144178932 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318082955/https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/pdf/10.2466/pr0.1975.36.2.467 | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2021-03-18}}</ref>

研究员佩勒姆、米伦伯格、琼斯2002根据卡斯勒的第一种解释深入研究后提出，人类有自我感觉良好的基本欲望，行为受这种本能驱使。这些积极联想自动产生，影响几乎所有涉及[[自我|自我]]的情感。根据[[禀赋效应|纯粹所有权效应]]，人类对拥有的事物印象更好。研究人员据此提出，人类会对与关系自我的事物产生感情，姓名也不例外。<ref name="Joubert">{{cite journal | last = Joubert | first = Charles E. | title = Factors Related To Individuals Attitudes Toward Their Names | journal = Psychological Reports | volume = 57 | issue = 3 | page = 983 | year = 1985 | doi = 10.2466/pr0.1985.57.3.983 | s2cid = 143641207}}</ref>{{refn|group="注"|研究表明人普遍喜欢自有姓名<ref name="Joubert" />，大量研究数据表明[[姓名字母效应|姓名字母效应]]影响很大：各人选择时明显倾向姓名包含的字母<ref>{{cite journal | last = Nuttin | first = Jozef M. | year = 1985 | title = Narcissism beyond Gestalt and awareness: The name–letter effect | journal = European Journal of Social Psychology | volume = 15 | issue = 3 | page = 353 | doi = 10.1002/ejsp.2420150309}}</ref>。}}这种下意识的本能人称“[[内隐自大|内隐自大]]”<ref name="Pelham">{{cite journal | last1 = Pelham | first1 = B. | last2 = Mirenberg | first2 = Matthew C. | last3 = Jones | first3 = John T. | title = Why Susie sells seashells by the seashore: Implicit egotism and major life decisions | journal = [[个性与社会心理学杂志|Journal of Personality and Social Psychology]] | volume = 82 | issue = 4 | pages = 479–480 | year = 2002 | doi = 10.1037/0022-3514.82.4.469 | pmid = 11999918 | s2cid = 1677153 | url = https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Why-Susie-sells-seashells-by-the-seashore%3A-implicit-Pelham-Mirenberg/99e658185f1a6df534b95c184c98a1ca7cbd8756 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210228225528/https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Why-Susie-sells-seashells-by-the-seashore%3A-implicit-Pelham-Mirenberg/99e658185f1a6df534b95c184c98a1ca7cbd8756 | archive-date = 2021-02-28 | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>。尤里·西蒙逊认为，内隐自大仅在人几乎完全不在乎各选项差异时有效，对职业这类重大抉择不适用。如果决策风险很小，如挑选慈善机构，那么内隐自大产生影响的可能更大。<ref name="Simonsohn">{{cite journal | last1 = Simonsohn | first1 = Uri | title = Spurious? Name similarity effects (implicit egotism) in marriage, job, and moving decisions | journal = Journal of Personality and Social Psychology | volume = 101 | issue = 1 | pages = 23, 46 | year = 2011 | doi = 10.1037/a0021990 | pmid = 21299311 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210427044746/https://repository.upenn.edu/oid_papers/233/ | url = https://repository.upenn.edu/oid_papers/233/ | access-date = 2021-08-05 | ref = harv | archive-date = 2021-04-27 | dead-url = no }}</ref>雷蒙德·斯梅茨提出，如果内隐自大源于自我认同，那么缺乏自尊、自信的人很可能立场不受自我影响，甚至可能与内隐自大截然相反。他的理论已获实验室证实。<ref name="Smeets">{{cite book | last = Smeets | first = Raymond | title = On the Preference for Self-related Entities: The Role of Positive Self-associations in Implicit Egotism Effects | location = Nijmegen, the Netherlands | publisher = UB Nijmegen | year = 2009 | isbn = 978-90-90-24290-3 | pages = 11, 14}}</ref>

=== 实证研究 ===
[[File:Official_portrait_of_Lord_Judge_crop_2,_2019.jpg|thumb]]

姓名与工作契合的人对当年职业选择说法不一。前[[英格蘭及威爾斯首席法官|英格蘭及威爾斯首席法官]][[伊戈尔·贾奇|伊戈尔·贾奇]]自称小时候没听过任何人说他注定要当法官{{refn|group="注"|姓氏“贾奇”原文“{{lang|en|Judge}}”，意为法官。}}，“可以肯定，我的情况纯属巧合，我没发现任何迹象与此抵触。”詹姆斯·康塞尔与父亲、兄弟姐妹，还有两名远亲都是律师{{refn|group="注"|name="Counsell"|“康塞尔”原文“{{lang|en|Counsell}}”与“律师”原文“{{lang|en|counsellor}}”接近。}}，据称他很小就在家人敦促下立志投身法律事业，压根儿没想过干别的。<ref name="Michalos" />美国律师苏·姚称多年前许多听过她名字的人劝她当律师，可能对她的决定有影响{{refn|group="注"|人名“苏”原文“{{lang|en|Sue}}”有“起诉”之意。}}<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303499204576390082223366812 | title = Dr. Chopp, Meet Congressman Weiner | date = 2011-06-21 | accessdate = 2021-08-05 | newspaper = The Wall Street Journal | last1 = Silverman | first1 = Rachel Emma | last2 = Light | first2 = Joe | archivedate = 2021-04-20 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210420234405/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303499204576390082223366812 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。[[斯托姆·菲尔德|斯托姆·菲尔德]]与父亲[[弗兰克·菲尔德|弗兰克·菲尔德]]都是天气预报员，他在父亲影响下走上职业道路，但说不准名字到底有没有影响{{refn|group="注"|人名“斯托姆”原文“{{lang|en|Storm}}”意为“风暴”。}}<ref>{{cite news | last = Nelson | first = Graham | title = Meet ordinary humans whose names shaped their destiny | dead-url = yes | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/titoshandmadevodka/ | newspaper = [[赫芬顿邮报|The Huffington Post]] | accessdate = 2016-12-23 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160216081812/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/titoshandmadevodka/ | archivedate = 2016-02-16}}</ref>。心理学教授刘易斯·利普西特一生致力收集标名<ref>{{cite journal | last = Cole | first = Kristen | title = Is work calling your name? | journal = George Street Journal | volume = 25 | issue = 17 | url = http://www.brown.edu/Administration/George_Street_Journal/vol25/25GSJ17h.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080906163752/http://www.brown.edu/Administration/George_Street_Journal/vol25/25GSJ17h.html | date = 2001-02-09 | archivedate = 2008-09-06 | deadurl = yes | access-date = 2016-12-23}}</ref>，上课讲授姓名决定论时学生指出，利普西特教授还研究婴儿吮吸行为，所以也是姓名决定论的例证，利普西特表示“我还真没想到”{{refn|group="注"|姓氏“利普西特”原文“{{lang|en|Lipsitt}}”前半截“{{lang|en|lip}}”意为嘴唇，后半截“{{lang|en|sitt}}”与“{{lang|en|suck}}”（“吮吸”）发音相近。}}<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Nevid | first1 = Jeffrey S. | last2 = Rathus | first2 = Spencer A. | title = Psychology and the Challenges of Life - Adjustment and Growth | page = 202 | url = https://archive.org/details/psychologychalle0000nevi | location = Hoboken, New Jersey | publisher = John Wiley & Sons | year = 2009 | isbn = 978-0-470-38362-9 | access-date = 2021-08-05}}</ref>。[[英格蘭教會|英格蘭教會]]教区牧师迈克尔·维克斯自称姓氏与当教区牧师完全没关系{{refn|group="注"|姓氏“维克斯”原文“{{lang|en|Vickers}}”与“教区牧师”原文“{{lang|en|vicar}}”接近。}}，还称“大家不会根据姓名选职业，有时偏要对着干”<ref name="Colls" />。

针对美国牙科从业人员的研究表明，起名“丹尼斯”的男子往往与牙医关系密切{{refn|group="注"|“丹尼斯”原文“{{lang|en|Dennis}}”与“牙医”（“{{lang|en|dentist}}”）接近。}}<ref name="Fowler-2012" />{{rp|6}}。[[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]]研究发现，名字普通的学生辍学率比较低，名字特殊的学生相反<ref name="Bateson-Martin">{{cite book | last1 = Bateson | first1 = Patrick | last2 = Martin | first2 = Paul | title = Design for a Life: How Biology and Psychology Shape Human Behavior | publisher = Touchstone | location = New York | year = 2001 | isbn = 978-0-684-86933-9 | access-date = 2021-08-05 | page = [https://archive.org/details/designforlifehow00bate/page/124/mode/2up 124] | url = https://archive.org/details/designforlife00patr}}</ref>。学者认为这可能是因为姓名选择反映父母脾气，反过来影响下一代未来的行为。
